The paper deals with computer vision and video processing, specifically background subtraction, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed algorithm is based on a fully-convolutional neural network, which suggests that it may also fall under the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions data augmentation techniques, which could potentially place it under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm is based on metrics such as F-measure, recall, and precision, which are commonly used in the field of neural networks and machine learning, suggesting that it may also fall under the sub-category of neural networks (cs.NE).
